'''August Schmierer''' (born April 28, 1870, date of death unknown) was a [[Germany|German]] [[rugby union]] player who competed in the [[1900 Summer Olympics]].

He was a member of the German rugby union team, which won the silver medal. Germany was represented at the tournament mainly by the [[SC 1880 Frankfurt|FC 1880 Frankfurt]] rather than an official national team.<ref>[http://www.rugby-verband.de/cms/index.php?id=75 Die Gr<U+00FC>nderjahre des deutschen Rugbysports] {{de icon}} DRV website - Foundation years, accessed: 3 April 2010</ref> Schmierer had left Frankfurt in 1897 and was in 1900 already chairman of the [[Cannstatter Fu<U+00DF>ball-Club]]. But he was invited to the olympic tournament by his former club.<ref>{{cite book |title=Erinnerungen an den Cannstatter Fussball-Club |language = German |trans_title = Memories of the Cannstatter Fussball-Club |last=Heineken |first=Philipp |year=1930 |publisher=Verlag Hermann Meister |location=Heidelberg |pages=86<U+2013>88}}</ref>

